New Records: Zimbabwe extended their unbeaten run in the African Cup of Nations 2025 qualifiers following the Group J match week third game.
Key Match Events: Khama Billiat converted the penalty from the spot minutes after half an hour in the 34th minute to secure the win for Zimbabwe
Namibia had multiple shots hit the woodwork but were unable to produce any key chances to open their points tally in the qualification campaign.
Post-Match Reflections: Collin Benjamin praised his team's spirited performance despite being unable to pick a single point in Group J
Michael Nees guided his team to claim their first three points of the campaign and claimed the top place in the points table.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played at the Orlando Stadium in South Africa
Zimbabwe's Khama Billiat marked his return to the national team with the winner for his country
Others: Namibia National Football Team is sitting at the bottom of the table with zero points in Group J
Zimbabwe National Football Team secured their maiden three-point haul in the qualification campaign
